# Component Architecture

## Structure

- Keep the homepage and future pages composed from small, focused components in `components/`.
- Extract shared UI into reusable components before duplicating markup.
- Put shared logic in `lib/` and shared TypeScript shapes in `types/`.
- Keep `app/` thin: routing, layout, metadata, and page composition only.

## Conventions

- Prefer Server Components unless client interactivity is required.
- Preserve existing CSS class names when migrating or refactoring markup.
- Do not introduce new styling systems (e.g. Tailwind) without approval.
- Match existing naming, file layout, and composition patterns in the repo.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — monolithic page with duplicated card markup
export default function Page() {
  return <main>{/* 200 lines of repeated card HTML */}</main>;
}

// ✅ GOOD — composed from existing section components
export default function Page() {
  return (
    <main className="page-shell">
      <Hero />
      <AboutCard />
    </main>
  );
}
```
